attributes.name: malicious
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that detected the file as malicious.

attributes.name: undetected
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that didn't detected the file.

attributes.name: failure
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that failed scanning the file.

attributes.name: type_unsupported
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that don't support the file's type.

attributes.name: exiftool
attributes.documentation: Dictionary that contains the information generated by ExifTool for the file being scanned. Both keys and values are strings. ExifTool generates numeric values for some properties, but values in YARA dictionaries must have the same time, therefore they are converted to strings.

attributes.name: first_submission_date
attributes.documentation: Date on which the file was submitted to VirusTotal for the first time, as a UNIX timestamp.

attributes.name: file_name
attributes.documentation: File's name as it was last submitted to VirusTotal.

attributes.name: file_size
attributes.documentation: File size in bytes.

attributes.name: file_type
attributes.documentation: One of the types listed in the file types table (vt.FileType).

attributes.name: file_type_tags
attributes.documentation: Tags associated to the file's type, as listed in the file types table.

attributes.name: version
attributes.documentation: Version of the Golang compiler used.

attributes.name: arch
attributes.documentation: Target architecture for a Golang binary.

attributes.name: os
attributes.documentation: Target OS for a Golang binary.

attributes.name: build_id
attributes.documentation: Build ID of Golang binary.

attributes.name: deps
attributes.documentation: Golang binary's dependencies.

attributes.documentation: Golang package path.

attributes.documentation: Version of the dependency package used.

attributes.documentation: Dictionary where keys are setting names and values are the setting value.

attributes.documentation: Total number of dependencies for a Golang binary.

attributes.documentation: Total number of interfaces in a Golang binary.

attributes.name: num_types
attributes.documentation: Total number of types in a Golang binary.

attributes.documentation: Number of functions from standard library used by a Golang binary.

attributes.documentation: Number of user-defined functions in a Golang binary.

attributes.name: imphash
attributes.documentation: File's import hash.

attributes.name: new_file
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) True if the file is being submitted to VirusTotal for the first time.

attributes.name: magic
attributes.documentation: File's type as returned by Linux's file command.

attributes.name: dhash
attributes.documentation: Hash that clusters together files with similar icons or thumbnails.

attributes.name: raw_md5
attributes.documentation: MD5 of the icon associated to the file.

attributes.name: malware_families
attributes.documentation: List of family names produced from a malware config extraction process. Samples with malware configs can be obtained searching have:malware_config, family names will be displayed in the detections tab under "Malware config detection" or in the details tab under "Malware configuration file" where there is the full report.

attributes.name: md5
attributes.documentation: File's MD5.

attributes.name: sha1
attributes.documentation: File's SHA1.

attributes.name: sha256
attributes.documentation: File's SHA256.

attributes.name: signatures
attributes.documentation: Dictionary where keys are antivirus names and values are malware signatures. The casing for both antivirus names and signatures is exactly as they appear in the web reports or API responses.

attributes.name: ssdeep
attributes.documentation: File's ssdeep hash.

attributes.name: subfile
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) True if the file being scanned is not the one submitted to VirusTotal but one derived from it. For example, when a PE file packed with UPX is submitted to VirusTotal, both the original file and the unpacked file are scanned. This is true for the unpacked file and false for the original packed one.

attributes.name: city
attributes.documentation: City from where the file was submitted, referred to the last submission. All lowercases.

attributes.name: country
attributes.documentation: Country from where the file was submitted, referred to the last submission. This is a two-letter ISO 3166 country code, in uppercase.

attributes.name: tags
attributes.documentation: File's tags.

attributes.name: tlsh

attributes.documentation: Number of times the file has been submitted to VirusTotal. This is 1 for the first submission.

attributes.documentation: Number of unique sources that have submitted this file.
